# Defense-in-depth: keep credentials and local cruft out of the build context so
# they can never land in an image layer. The Dockerfile copies only src/, data/,
# pyproject.toml, and README.md today, but this guards against a future COPY . .
.env
.env.*
.git/
.venv/
.sessions/
**/__pycache__/
*.pyc
.DS_Store
